item.title: Variables
item.description: Uninitialized variables Uninitialized variables have an initial value of null. Even variables with numeric types are initially null, because numbers are objects. void main() { var a; num b; int c; double d; bool e; print(a); // null print(b); // null print(c); // null print(d); // null print(e); // null }
